    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>Transits of HD 189733 with ALMA</prj:name>
        <prj:note>This goal of this proposal is to verify the shape of the light curve at radio wavelength with observations of planetary transits with the Atacama Large Millimeter/Submillimeter Array radio interferometer. We plan to analyze both limb brightening that provides information on the chromospheric temperature structure and also on the influence of active region which intensity decrease will give clues about the magnetic fields within these regions.A spectra of the radio emission of the active star HD 189733 will also be obtained to determine the emission mechanism from its corona.</prj:note>
