        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>From a list of planet hosting stars, we selected the most promising one that is HD 189733. This is a young star of estimated age of 0.6 Gyr and is known to be magnetically active with spots on its surface (Pont et al. 2007). We propose to observe at least 5 transits of this star at 345 GHz.</prj:justificationText>
